<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Body length (excluding antennae) of adults: holotype 1.0 mm, male 1.1 mm, females 0.9-1.3 mm. Habitus typical of genus. Color dark bluish-black, paler ventrally, eye-patches dark. Granulation fine and uniform, 7-10 granules between chaetae p1 on Abd. V (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Ant. IV with simple apical vesicle, subapical organite (or), microsensillum (ms), two lateral and three dorsal long thin and curved blunt sensilla (S7, S8 + S1, S2, S3 in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4A</figureCitation>
). Ant. III-organ with two long (outer) and two short (inner) sensilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4A</figureCitation>
). Microsensillum on Ant. III present. Ant. I with eight chaetae (chaeta 
<normalizedToken originalValue="p’">p'</normalizedToken>
present).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Ocelli 8 + 8. Postantennal organ 1.5-1.8 larger than neighboring ocellus, with four subequal lobes of which anterior pair larger than posterior one. Accessory boss present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4B</figureCitation>
). Labrum with four distinct apical papillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4E</figureCitation>
). Labral chaetae 5, 5, 4, prelabrals 4. Maxillary head of the 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. tullbergi" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="tullbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">H. tullbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type (
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe royale zoologique de Belgique" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="89 - 99" refId="B8" refString="Fjellberg, A, 1984. Maxillary structures in Hypogastruridae (Collembola). Annales de la Societe royale zoologique de Belgique 114 (1): 89 - 99" title="Maxillary structures in Hypogastruridae (Collembola)." volume="114" year="1984">Fjellberg 1984</bibRefCitation>
) and labium as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="309 - 330" refId="B11" refString="Fjellberg, A, 1999. The Labial Palp in Collembola. Zoologischer Anzeiger 237: 309 - 330" title="The Labial Palp in Collembola." volume="237" year="1999">Fjellberg (1999)</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4C</figureCitation>
). Outer lobe of maxilla with two sublobal hairs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Tibiotarsi I, II, III with 19, 19, 18 chaetae respectively. Apical chaeta A1 long pointed or blunt. Claws with small inner tooth. Empodial appendage with broad basal lamella and apical filament reaching slightly beyond inner tooth of unguis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Chaetotaxy of head typical of genus, with complete set of v-chaetae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov A, B dorsal chaetotaxy C, D ventral chaetotaxy. Scale: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439540" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">3A</figureCitation>
). Chaetae short and smooth. Body sensilla (s) about two times longer than ordinary chaetae, fine and smooth. Dorsal chaetotaxy as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov A, B dorsal chaetotaxy C, D ventral chaetotaxy. Scale: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439540" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">3A, B</figureCitation>
. Th. I with 3 + 3 chaetae. Th. II with chaetae m2, m3, m4 and m5 present, m6' and m6 absent. Th. III with chaetae m3, m4 and m5 present, m2 and m6' absent and chaeta m6 usually absent (rarely present). Abd. IV with chaetae p3 and p7 present, and with chaetae m1 to m6 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="68" start="start">present</pageBreakToken>
. On Abd. V chaetae p2 present (2+2 chaetae between s-chaetae) and m-chaetae absent. Subcoxae1 of legs I, II, III with 1, 3, 3 chaetae respectively. Microsensillum on Th. II present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
Ventral chaetotaxy as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov A, B dorsal chaetotaxy C, D ventral chaetotaxy. Scale: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439540" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">3C, D</figureCitation>
. Ventral tube with four chaetae on each side. Retinaculum with 4 + 4 teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="69" start="start">Furca</pageBreakToken>
well developed (ratio dens+mucro/inner edge of claw III 2.5-3.5). Dens without tooth-like granules and ventro-apical swelling. Dorsal side of dens with fine granulation (the granules become enlarged towards apex) and seven chaetae. Mucro with relatively high outer lamella. Ratio dens/mucro 3.5-4.5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">4I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
Anal spines small, situated on high basal papillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hypogastrura herrerosvelai sp. nov. A ant. III-IV chaetotaxy B PAO and eyes C labium (A-E labial papillae) D maxillary palp E labrum F axial chaetotaxy and granulation on Abd. V G, H anal spines in lateral (G) and dorsal (H) view I Dens and mucro J Tibiotarsus and claw III. Scales: 0.03 mm (10, 12, 14 - 19), 0.02 mm (11, 13)." figureDoi="10.3897/subtbiol.35.54257.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/439541" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">4G, H</figureCitation>
), ratio anal spine/basal papilla 0.5-0.7, ratio anal spine+basal papilla/inner edge of claw III 0.9-1.0.
</paragraph>
